\par
\f3\ltrch\u-10179?\u-8998?\f1\lang1033  \f0 Source\f7\rtlch\lang1037\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 While the exact phrase doesn\f1\lang1037\rquote\f0\lang1033 t appear in Pound\f1\lang1037\rquote\f0\lang1033 s major works like ABC of Reading or The Cantos, it reflects his core belief in art as a vessel for emotional and cultural permanence.\f7\rtlch\lang1037\par
\par
\f0\ltrch\lang1033 So while we don\f1\lang1037\rquote\f0\lang1033 t have a pinpointed publication or date, the phrase lives on as a kind of distilled Poundian ethos\f1\lang1037\emdash\f0\lang1033 one that Ginsberg and others helped carry forward.\f7\rtlch\lang1037\par
